
Notes on the auto-updater

Interactive mode:
Lists installed product(s), and available versions.
The user can select products and update them.

Automatic mode:
Automatically retrieves the latest version of the selected product
and updates it.

Each product has a separate meta-info page which provides the following
information for each patch:

Product

Patch version
Architecture {x86,ppc,alpha,etc}
Updates version(s)
Diskspace required
Patch URL

.
.
.

Recommended patch file names:
product-version-{incremental|full}-arch.run


Updater process:

Check for loki_update updates
Apply any pending updates, restart if patched

Check for installed products
Check for new versions of products
Prompt to apply updates
